Results.ReviewText:
The two things I've never scrimped on are loo rolls (the one with puppies) and instant coffee (Gold Blend) and that's a rule I've stuck to ever since I bought my first house and no matter how rich or poor I've been.

I have espresso machines, cafetieres and a big coffee machine. But sometimes there's nothing better than dunking a rich tea biscuit in a mug of Gold Blend and when you get to the last swallow taking the coffee and the biscuit bits together. Not any more. Apart from the awful weird taste, the gunge at the bottom means you can't finish off the coffee and biscuit bits. One of life's few pleasures have been removed from me.

I've now stopped buying GB. I'll buy one again if I see "new" or "improved" on the label in the hope that sanity has been restored.

I have to give it 1 star - it's wet. I also notice that the 5 starZ reviews seem to be from a number of those who have received a free product. Nescafe shouldn't rely on them too much and should concentrate on the opinions of those who've supported you for decades.
Results.Title: A failed experiment?

ClientResponses.Response: It's really sad to hear you're not a fan of the changes we've made but thanks for leaving your feedback.
